A N A C T
RELATING TO FISH AND WILDLIFE -- LOBSTERS AND OTHER CRUSTACEANS --
BLUE CRABS
Introduced By: Representatives Roberts, Quattrocchi, Place, Hopkins, J. Brien, Fascia,
and Nardone
Date Introduced: February 26, 2025
Referred To: House Environment and Natural Resources
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 20-7-15 of the General Laws in Chapter 20-7 entitled "Lobsters and
2 Other Crustaceans" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 20-7-15. Taking of blue crabs.
4 Unless otherwise specified by regulation, no person shall take, or attempt to take, any blue
5 crabs from any of the waters in this state except by a scoop or crab net, trot, or hand line. Taking
6 of blue crabs shall be restricted to residents of this state.
7 There shall be no limit, rules or regulations, restricting the harvesting of blue crabs in the
8 state.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
